"Kang H., Zhuang H., Wu L., Liu Q., Shen G., Berg B., Man R., Liu C.","Variation in leaf nitrogen and phosphorus stoichiometry in Picea abies across Europe: An analysis based on local observations",2011,"Forest Ecology and Management","261","2",,"195","202",,,10.1016/j.foreco.2010.10.004,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-78649450458&partnerID=40&md5=068a15f85414899cd5c71807f64a5373","School of Agriculture and Biology, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, Dongchuan Rd. 800, Shanghai 200240, China; Department of Forest Ecology, University of Helsinki, FIN-00014 Helsinki, Finland; Ontario Forest Research Institute, Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources, 1235 Queen St. E. Sault Ste., Marie, ON P6A 2E5, Canada; Key Laboratory of Urban Agriculture (South), Ministry of Agriculture, People's Republic of China, Dongchuan Rd. 800, Shanghai 200240, China","Kang, H., School of Agriculture and Biology, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, Dongchuan Rd. 800, Shanghai 200240, China; Zhuang, H., School of Agriculture and Biology, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, Dongchuan Rd. 800, Shanghai 200240, China; Wu, L., School of Agriculture and Biology, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, Dongchuan Rd. 800, Shanghai 200240, China; Liu, Q., School of Agriculture and Biology, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, Dongchuan Rd. 800, Shanghai 200240, China; Shen, G., School of Agriculture and Biology, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, Dongchuan Rd. 800, Shanghai 200240, China; Berg, B., Department of Forest Ecology, University of Helsinki, FIN-00014 Helsinki, Finland; Man, R., Ontario Forest Research Institute, Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources, 1235 Queen St. E. Sault Ste., Marie, ON P6A 2E5, Canada; Liu, C., School of Agriculture and Biology, Shanghai Jiao Tong University, Dongchuan Rd. 800, Shanghai 200240, China, Key Laboratory of Urban Agriculture (South), Ministry of Agriculture, People's Republic of China, Dongchuan Rd. 800, Shanghai 200240, China","Nitrogen (N) and phosphorus (P) and N:P ratio in terrestrial plants and the patterns at a large geographical scale are an important issue in ecological stoichiometry. In particular, it is essential to know that for a single species, how the N:P stoichiometry varies with climatic factors in the context of global warming. Our analysis was based on a data set including 2583 observations at 441 sites on nutritional status of Norway spruce (Picea abies L.) located in European counties (including Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Czech Rep., Finland, Germany, Ireland, Italy, Lithuania, Norway, Slovak Rep., Slovenia, United Kingdom). Our objectives are to demonstrate how leaf N and P concentration and N:P ratio in Norway spruce vary with altitude (ALT), latitude (LAT), longitude (LON), mean annual temperature (MAT) and mean annual precipitation (MAP) across Europe. The results showed that for 1-year-old needles of Norway spruce, the N and P concentration were 13.28mgg-1, 1.41mgg-1 and the N:P ratio was 9.76. Leaf N displayed a convex curve pattern with increasing MAT and decreasing LAT from the boreal Europe to the Mediterranean area. The N concentration and N:P generally reached peak at about 7°C in MAT or 53° N in LAT. The N:P ratio varied non-linearly with LAT and MAP, but linearly with MAT. Leaf N concentration and N:P ratio decreased linearly with increasing ALT in temperate European area. Across Europe, that the patterns of leaf N and N:P ratio were mainly driven by climate-related geochemistry and plant physiology, but also greatly impacted by anthropogenic N deposition. © 2010 Elsevier B.V.","Climate; Geographical coordinates; Nitrogen; Norway spruce; Phosphorus; Stoichiometry","Austria; Belgium; Bulgaria; Climate; Climatic factors; Data sets; Ecological stoichiometry; Finland; Geographical coordinates; Geographical scale; Germany; Ireland; Leaf nitrogen; Lithuania; Mean annual precipitation; Mean annual temperatures; Mediterranean areas; N deposition; N:P ratio; Norway spruce; Picea abies; Plant physiology; Single species; Slovenia; Terrestrial plants; United kingdom; Analytical geochemistry; Concentration (process); Ecology; Global warming; Nitrogen; Phosphorus; Stoichiometry; anthropogenic effect; concentration (composition); data set; environmental factor; evergreen tree; geochemistry; global warming; latitude; leaf morphology; linearity; nitrogen; nutritional status; observational method; phosphorus; stoichiometry; temperature effect; terrestrial ecosystem; Europe; Picea abies",,,,,,"Ahti, T., Hämet-Ahti, L., Jalas, J., Vegetation zones and their sections in Northwestern Europe (1968) Ann. Bot. Fenn., 5, pp. 169-211; Andersson, F.O., Brække, F.H., Hallbäcken, F., (1998) Nutrition and Growth of Norway Spruce Forests in a Nordic Climatic and Deposition Gradient, , Nordic Council of Ministers, Copenhagen; Ägren, G.O.I., Stoichiometry and nutrition of plant growth in natural communities (2008) Annu. Rev. Ecol. Evol. S., 39, pp. 153-170; Bartnicki, J., Alcamo, J., Calculating nitrogen deposition in Europe (1989) Water Air Soil Poll., 47, pp. 101-123; Berg, B., Johansson, M.B., Meentemeyer, V., Litter decomposition in a transect of Norway spruce forests: substrate quality and climate control (2000) Can. J. Forest. Res., 30, pp. 1136-1147; Briceno-Elizondo, E., Garcia-Gonzalo, J., Peltola, H., Matala, J., Kellomaki, S., Sensitivity of growth of Scots pine Norway spruce and silver birch to climate change and forest management in boreal conditions (2006) Froest Ecol. Manag., 232, pp. 152-167; Cape, J.N., Freersmith, P.H., Paterson, I.S., Parkinson, J.A., Wolfenden, J., The Nutritional-status of Picea-Abies (L) Karst across Europe and implications for forest decline (1990) Trees-Struct. Funct., 4, pp. 211-224; Dise, N.B., Wright, R.F., Nitrogen leaching from European forests in relation to nitrogen deposition (1995) Froest Ecol. Manag., 71, pp. 153-161; (2001), http://www.fao.org/forestry/fo/fra/index.jsp, FAO, Forest Resources Assessment, 2000. FAO Forestry Paper 140. Rome (see