, 12, pp. 573-590; Oleksyn, J., Reich, P.B., Zytkowiak, R., Karolewski, P., Tjoelker, M.G., Nutrient conservation increases with latitude of origin in European Pinus sylvestris populations (2003) Oecologia, 136, pp. 220-235; Reich, P.B., Oleksyn, J., Global patterns of plant leaf N and P in relation to temperature and latitude (2004) P. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA., 101, pp. 11001-11006; Sah, S.P., Isotope ratios and concentration of N in needles, roots and soils of Norway spruce (Picea abies [L.] Karst.) stands as influenced by atmospheric deposition of N (2005) J. Forest Sci., 51, pp. 468-475; Seynave, I., Gegout, J.C., Herve, J.C., Dhote, J.F., Drapier, J., Bruno, E., Dume, G., Picea abies site index prediction by environmental factors and understorey vegetation: a two-scale approach based on survey databases (2005) Can. J. Forest. Res., 35, pp. 1669-1678; Stefan, K., Fürst, A., Hacker, R., Bartels, U., (1997) Forest Foliar Condition in Europe Technical Report, p. 88. , Austrian Federal Forest Research Centre, EC, UN/ECE, Vienna, Brussels Geneva; Stefan, K., Raitio, H., Bartels, U., Fürst, A., Rautio, P., (2000), Manual on Methods and Criteria for Harmonized Sampling, Assessment, Monitoring and Analysis of the Effects of Air Pollution on Forests. Part IV Sampling and Analysis of Needles and Leaves. PN UN/ECE, ICP. 2000Thompson, K., Parkinson, J.A., Band, S.R., Spencer, R.E., A comparative study of leaf nutrient concentrations in a regional herbaceous flora (1997) New Phytol., 136, pp. 679-689; Van de Waal, D.B., Verschoor, A.M., Verspagen, J.M.H., van Donk, E., Huisman, J., Climate-driven changes in the ecological stoichiometry of aquatic ecosystems (2010) Front. Ecol. Environ., 8, pp. 145-152; Vanmechelen, L., Groenemans, R., Van Ranst, E., (1997) Forest Soil Condition in Europe. Technical Report, p. 257. , Ministry of the Flemish Community, EC and UN/ECE, Brussels, Geneva; Vitousek, P.M., Turner, D.R., Kitayama, K., Foliar nutrients during long-term soil development i